      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "text": "Modal fallacies are formal fallacies in which modality plays a role in the fallaciousness of a type of argument. Modal Logic is the most general fallacy involving modalities, but most actual fallacious arguments involving modalities will commit the subfallacy, above.",
